Seven University of Nairobi students have urged court to throw out charges of creating disturbance in a manner likely to cause a breach of the peace.They are also accused of disobeying orders by Prof Peter Mbithi. The students, through lawyer Evans Ondieki, told trial magistrate Mutuku the 24 counts against them are unconstitutional and defective.They are Timothy Sikenyi, Arnold Odenyo, Samuel Mogaka, Michael Bonga, Maxwel Odiambo, David Osano and Franklin Odongo. They are accused of committing the offences on September 16 and 26 last year at University of Nairobi administration block.The magistrate case will be heard on March 24. They are out on a Sh5,000 bail each.